  "description": "The Solomon knot is a two-ring architecture: at strandTune=7.02, Ring A holds the root and Ring B holds the fifth. Two coupled ring oscillators, intra-ring coupling at 0.8, cross-ring at 0.3. macroKnot=0.35 nudges from Solomon toward Trefoil — the two-ring symmetry fractionally breaks, Ring A begins to acquire a directional pull from the Trefoil's asymmetric ring. The result: a bell-like decay where the inharmonic overtones slowly drift as the topology gradient shifts. Short attack, long exponential decay — each note is a ring being struck and watched.",
